properties.name: Rosslare Strand
properties.wheelchair:description: The trainstation is unmanned. Only platform 1 is in use. Toilets and waiting room are locked. Nearest public toilets are on the beach next to Watersports Centre.

properties.name: Dublin Heuston
properties.note: There's two reference systems used: a five-letter code and a numerical identifier. I've used the former (HSTON), the latter is 1. Both can be found on the Wikipedia station list - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_railway_stations_in_Ireland

properties.name: Galway Ceannt
properties.note: Note that the name "Galway Ceannt" / "Gaillimh Cheannt" is never translated as "Galway Kent" to avoid confusion with "Cork Kent".

properties.name: Dún Laoghaire Mallin
properties.note: Since every other station named for an Easter Rising figure had the name by default, I've swapped DL Mallin to name and DL to short_name.
